The article is about the White House Pride celebration, where the First Lady, Kamala Harris, Doug Emhoff, and Joe Biden welcomed attendees. The First Lady expressed her joy at being back at the White House together and mentioned a previous Pride event they attended in Las Vegas. She acknowledged the progress made for LGBTQ rights but also highlighted that there are still places where rights are under attack and discrimination persists. The First Lady emphasized the importance of courage in being oneself and fighting for equality. She introduced Javier Gomez, a young activist who has spoken out against discriminatory legislation and shared his own story. The article concludes at 4:26 P.M. EDT.